This paper is about a machine reading comprehension dataset, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Specifically, the paper focuses on bilingual and cross-lingual reading comprehension, which involves language translation and understanding. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and computational linguistics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these sub-categories also cover topics related to NLP and machine learning.
